caption.text:
"The Statue of Vishnu riding The Garuda"
As a man who are attracted to history, I really like to go to historical site because it could talk many things and I could fell the moment when I touched it....like going back a hundred years ago. For example this statue named Vishnu riding The Garuda. This statue told us about the life of Sang Winata (mother Garuda) who became slaves of the Kadru (mother of the Dragon), because of losing bets on the color of the horse Uchaisrawa. Originally the horse tail Uchaisrawa is all white. But at the behest of the Kadru against his son (the dragons) ultimately the tail of the Uchaisrawa Horse is sprinkled so that it changes its color to black. Since then Winata lost and became a slave to the Kadru.Garuda who felt sorry for the suffering of his mother, helped care for the children of the Kadru. At the request of Garuda, the Kadru wanted to free his mother from slavery on the condition of being given holy water (Amerta). In his quest Garuda met Lord Vishnu, who then said to Garuda: "Garuda, if you want Amerta, please ask me". Meanwhile God Wisnu asked Garuda to be willing to be his vehicle. That's why Garuda could be a vehicle for Vishnu.
I'm really sure that history teach us many things, and we can take advantages from them. So...never forget your history whatever it's gonna be happen because history reflects who you are.
Can you imagine how our ancestors made it? That's what we call as collective knowledge....really really awesome
FYI : The Garuda is a large legendary bird, bird-like creature, or humanoid bird that appears in both Hindu and Buddhist mythology.
#history#arts#statue#culture#knowledge#learning#kingdom#historyofindonesia

[Indonesia Health-Care Forum Innovation Award]
The most "nyesek" day in the life. 
When i was eating food in CC Barat, my friend called me and asked to come to his Medical Instrumentation Laboratory then I made as fast as possible. After I arrived there, he said that there was a Indo HCF announcement, the competition which followed. The announcement was reported by video in Facebook, we followed E-Health Category and after waiting for several minutes, it was the time for E-Health Category, we hoped we could be one of the finalist (only 1-5 team who can presentate their ideas in Jakarta) but maybe it was not our lucky day, we just got 6th position, suddenly we felt so upset, but something unique happen when the judge called my name, he said that something funny because my name is Gewinner sounds like the winner, hahaha, but the things that made us happy was the judge said our idea was very unique and original.
Until now, i feel so "nyesek" because maybe this is our last competition, at the first, we have a plan that being a champion is a must, but the reality is not.
One thing that we can get from this experience is the real champion is who always stand up  or work harder although he lost until he reach his dream. The most hard worker and brilliant partner ever @mdzakyfauzanm , thank you for always supporting me, we had followed many competitions right....

Autonomous Underwater Robot [Percobaan 1]
Robot ini bergerak dengan cara mengikuti garis kuning (line follower). Robot dapat mengikuti garis menggunakan kamera HP yang telah dibuat programnya terlebih dahulu dengan android studio, kemudian hasil bacaan berupa garis-garis akan dikirim via Bluetooth dan akan diolah oleh microcontroller arduino, data data tersebut digunakan sebagai referensi untuk menggerakkan motor (pengaturan pwm).
